content: It's not a terrible game. The power controls are a bit janky, and at full power, all of the drivers (FD to Destroyer) max out at about the same distance. The only difference is the amount of anny required to get the flex you want.

If I had to boil down my issues with this game into one word it would be simple.  Putting.  The interface for putting in this game is awful. It's completely and totally random. You pull back, flick forward and wonder what happens next! There are plenty of great UI concepts for sports games for things like putting, free throw shooting, etc. Why this game refused to adopt any of these is beyond me.  Since course and player progression is based around performance on holes the inability to putt consistently creates an instant wall in the game.  Hopefully the putting interface gets an overhaul in the future. For now though, this game is unplayable to me.

One of the better disc golf games on the market.  It really does capture the fun of going out and playing without actually going out and playing; however, it's marred by control inconsistencies.  It's fairly annoying to go for a simple 150ft upshot and having the controls freak out and send you a measly 50ft.  The putting is also horribly inconsistent.  The same swipe from 30 feet out can land 15ft short or go sailing over the basket. If you do happen to make it into the basket, there's a 50% chance that the rubber band chains will spit the disc back out at you.  Control issues aside, it's a fun game.  Launching a disc just right and watching it weave its way around the course is almost as satisfying as doing it for real, and it's a great way to kill time.

Same stroke gets different results, putting is atrocious. Gameplay is cool, good graphics and physics too, but it is maddening to continually dump coins into a skill and see no tangible results
Awesome and realistic game which makes it perfect!

Awesome representation of the sport. Best app available on the market. Developer adding unique courses regularly, love the inclusion of Nokia. Keep up the great work, would love to see the ability to play a round against other players in a multi-player environment!
Love the graphics and gameplay. Worth the money.

The game needs many tweeks and improvements.  It would be nice to have a score card you can view at anytime! I would like to know the basket, shots currently taken, par for that basket at anytime!      Overall, the game is a blast and I dont really do games. Will give 5 stars in future with additional changes and tweaks. Great job dev team!
Best disc golf game ever
Game works very well and is really fun to play.
It'd be nice to start with like a starter 3 pack of basic discs instead of one midrange. Great game tho.
Just like the real deal, I just wish there were more than 27 holes.
When I cannot play disc golf, I can play this game!
Flight physics seem to be spot on. This game could really use a practice putting/driving mode though to give players a chance to get the hang of the mechanics.

This game is worth the 4 dollars if you like discgolf. You can only throw backhand. Lefty or righty. I recommend enabling the simple aim control in options before you play. Your swipe can send an overstable driver to the right without adjusting the disc towards anhyzer. The simplified aim option visually displays your discs flight options. It would be nice to see a feature allowing you to lean out from trees.

I absolutely love it. It's very addicting. Sometimes I have a stellar round, other times I get so frustrated I want to throw my phone, just like in real disc golf, lol. While I'm very happy with disc selection and flight patterns, there are a couple additions I hope to see in a future update. Being able to choose your stance would be great, i.e. regular putting stance past 49 feet or leaning out around trees. Also, being able to choose different throwing options; side-arm, overhead, rollers, etc. Thank you.
Good game but but it keeps freezing
Great game, more courses please
Very realistic and well executed.
Amazing game!

This is an excellent disc golf game. The disc flight is beautiful and seems fairly accurate.  It takes a while to figure out how to throw but that is the same for disc golf in the real world.  I like how you must release the putt at the right level and it took me a while before I realized it wasn't going to work with a full swipe of the finger.  Please keep improving this game, it would be nice if you could lean out on a shot, throw forehands, rollers and thumber/tomahawks and it would be nice if you could skip the disc instead of it always skidding when it hits the ground.  Alternate camera angles and replays would be nice too.  Keep up the good work!
Awesome game! Lots of fun! Can get old since there are only three courses.
By far the best mobile disc golf game. Can't wait for more courses, discs, and throwing techniques.
I played almost all tees to 2 stars in one night.. Need more courses! :)

This game is so inconsistent it's infuriating!!! I was doing the same thing and getting 20 different results. I had such high hopes for this game. But you're trying make it to realistic that you've made it hard to control. Remember it's a video game for phones and tablets not a console. I'm so glad I could get a refund on my purchase.
Needs better power gauge and aiming, throwing some shots way right or left even if my finger stays in the middle of the screen.

I really like this game but I think there needs to be bonuses.  Like when I sink a 100 foot putt.  Should be worth a 100bucks or something.  There needs to be achievements so I have something to play for.  I really love disc golf but there aren't many courses in Iraq.  This is all the DG I have for now.

Very fun and very addicting, and more realistic than anything else out there. Its not easy by any means but its not impossible either, but expect a lot of pars. It starts you out with enough coins to buy a couple discs or a disc and some upgrades, it seems some people just didn't use common sense in regards to spending their coins wisely. I do however agree that the coin earning system takes way too long to be able to upgrade your player or buy additional discs. Adding a forehand shot would also be nice to keep things interesting. The putting is hard, but putting is also hard in real life so...but it would be nice if you could choose to putt from outside the circle because doing the touch shots from 40 feet out is impossible to make. Overall I think its a great game.

i played last night until battery drained completely (even while charging), but when i woke up this morning to start the game again, i get to the hole intro screen where it says "tap to play" and as soon as i touch the screen it stops and drive direction line shows (with animation) but still nothing else happens. completely halts on that screen, any ideas?  i had to reinstall game, start all over...
replyContent: Thank you for reporting. This is the first time I hear of this problem. I don't know why it happened but I will try to make that happen and fix it. Do you remember where were you in game when battery went off ?

content: This is quite hard. Takes a while to handle shots. That's not bad thing at all. Great job and thanks for the game! :)
Fantastic game.  Would love to see more courses.  I'd even be willing to pay for them to support this developer.  Very impressed by the game.
It is a great game! But would be better if it showed flight path or showed where the disc will land if thrown the way it says to throw. And a power meter to show how much power is in your throw.
Disc golf is the best thing ever, love the game and how much work that was put into it. Hopefully there willl be more updates with more courses and discs now (:
I open the app today after weeks of playing/progressing and everything's been reset..stats.. coins...and holes/courses I'd unlocked...
Great.  Beginning is difficult but as you level putting gets easier.  I would love rollers or sidearm options.  And the more holes the better!
Best mobile disc golf game I've played yet.
No matter what, every first throw (drive) only goes 50m. Every 2nd throw over 75m. EVERY TIME. Very inconsistent control/ input.
The flight patterns are great.  I can't put the phone down.
Seems accurate.
few bugs but will be get over time like a good wine

Add replays, add sharing for those replays, add multi-player, add leader boards with friends, more courses, more discs of course. Very frustrating chain outs love it just like the real thing. However, I think a bit more on touch=accuracy/power, maybe fine tune it a bit? And the flippy screen thing is annoying when trying to power throw and you tilt your phone too much it flips the screen and screws up your shot. Uhm. An escape button from the throwing incase you accidentally touch it or change your mind. ❤

I really like this game. Nice supplement for those days I can't go play the real thing. A few things I would like to see though. Maybe the ability to throw some rollers or side arm. Also the coin system is pretty hard. I know you don't want to make it too easy. But, I have only been able to buy 1 driver. And it is talking forever to move up in skills. Also trading in discs would be a bonus.

As others noted, there are some issues.  Overall though it's great.  Things I've noticed... putting is very inconsistent until you get maybe 10 extra points in it, but IRL a 30 foot put is 1 in 5 for me at best.  Getting a max distance flex shot is hard too, but also hard for me IRL.  Tweaks I'd like. 1. Powering down is near impossible, making island holes a big pain. 2. End holes or rounds early. 3. Login option so I can play same profile on android or ipad.
The grapics are sick. The physics are sick. The discs are sick. Love this game
Please either give me back my 4 dollars or put some customize in this game . Please fix or update this game
Great physics and flight paths. Very impressed. Any play to add new discs or courses?
Great physics
The mechanics are spot on and the gameplay is challenging. Hopefully we can see a few more courses and discs added onto this game in the future.
I now have a new game to pass the time. Best disc golf game by far.

Wow, congrats on creating the first disc golf game I've ever played that actually has realistic flight characteristics.  These discs actually fade at the end and you can really get a sense of each disc's stability! Which means you can throw a big hyzer or an S turn depending on what you want to do, disc behaves believably!  Can't wait to play real courses with this kind of physics, someday. Totally worth the money as a game.

Helposti paras frisbeegolf-peli. Muutama ehdotus pelin parantamiseksi. Varjot puihin, tai edes koriin. Kiekon vaihtaminen voisi olla nopeampaa, eli voisi olla vaikka 3x4 ruudukko mistä kiekon voi vaihtaa. Ohjeisiin joku selkeytys siitä miten oikeasti heitetään, eli onko sormen nopeudella ja suunnalla paljonkin väliä. Tiheä metsä rata! Uusinta jolla voi katsoa miten heitto meni, kamera voisi seurata kiekkoa uusinnassa. Asetus musiikin mutettamiseen. Näitä riittää viellä lisää jos haluat kuulla :D

What a disappointment this game ended up being. If I'm going to pay $4 for a game. I expect it to be fully unlocked. No instructions at all on how to play or operate the game. I ended up "accidentally" spending my 2500 coins it starts you out with on my power meter because the power meter gives you no indication you have spent any coins on it. Furthermore the game starts you off with a putter....... $4 and it won't even start you with the basics like a driver and mid range. Avoid.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback. I wanted it to be part of the game that you will unlock holes to play. I didn't want to give 3 discs at start because I want the player to buy the discs he/she likes. Game starts with one midrange and money to buy another 2. There are no in app purchases to get money. You have to earn them by playing.

content: Over all play is well but def. Need to change when you go ob you should play the last place it was in bounds not where you just threw. And is it just me or is everyone having a problem with judging power sometimes it goes really far sometimes he just flops it up there it doesnt seem like there is a real good judge of how far a disc will go if i throw it properly.
I don't want to put my phone down because this game is that good but I have to. My phone is literally getting too hot to touch. Also my battery went from 65% to 15% in 30 minutes. Using a nexus 6.
This is definitely the most realistic disc golf game out.
Missä kämmenheitot?? Lisäksi odottelen tuloslistoja (esim. fb:n kautta), heiton replay-toimintoa ja laajempaa kiekkovalikoimaa.
Game is really nice, probably the best disc golf game out there, although after some time I was unable to play, cause game crashed every time I tried to start a course.
